OL,3,CWales obesity rates higher than any
OL,4,Cother UK nation, charity says
OL,6,FMore than a third of Welsh adults are
OL,7,Festimated to be obese, a charity has
OL,8,Fwarned, as new data reveals the
OL,9,Fproblem may be worse than previously
OL,10,Fthought.
OL,12,FOfficial figures have previously
OL,13,Fclassed 26% of adults in Wales as
OL,14,Fobese. However, analysis by the
OL,15,Finnovation charity Nesta says the true
OL,16,Ffigure is 34%.
OL,18,FThis would make Wales the nation
OL,19,Fwithrate in the UK, followed by
OL,20,FScotland (29%), Northern Ireland (27%)
OL,21,Fand England (26%).
