OL,6,FThis then leads to an underestimation
OL,7,Fof their body mass index (BMI),
OL,8,Faffecting the overall data pool.
OL,10,FEngland and Scotland also use a self-
OL,11,Freport model.
OL,13,FHowever, the data gathered is then
OL,14,Fadjusted to account for human error
OL,15,Fand underestimation.
OL,17,FThis differs from Northern Ireland's
OL,18,Fobesity figures, which are collected
OL,19,Fby professionals and based on an
OL,20,Findividual's height and weight.
